.SH NAME
SIMPLE SHELL

.PP
.B simple_shell man page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B
#include "shell.h"

simple_shell [option...] [arguments ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B
The simple_shell is a shell based program,that uses a command line interface(CLI).
The users inputs datas(human-readable),using the keyboard interface. 
Then the progam reads, converts, compiles,and executes the commands in a standard output.


.SH EXAMPLES FOR STANDARD INPUT COMMANDS

.TS
center box tab(#);
l s s 
r | r c.
STANDARD INPUT LISTS
_
ls#list directory contents.
_
ls -l#List in long format file system type.
_
pwd# will display the present working directory.
_
rm# will remove a file.
_
mv# will move or rename one or more files or directories.
_
cp# Will copy SOURCE to DEST.
_
exit# cause normal process termination.
_
ctrl + d, ctrl + c# stop the prompt input.
.TE

.SH RETURN VALUE
.B
If the program succed the return value is 0. 
If there is an issue,(end of the child process),an error message is displayed.
A new prompt is returning by the simple_shell process.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.B
In interactive mode, to exit the simple_shell usethis commands: [CTRL + D] or [CTRL + C].
Else, you have nothing to do, the execution will be aborded.

.SH BUILTINS
.B
.TS
center box tab(|);
l  s  s 
r | r  c .
BUILTINS LISTS
_
fgets()| reads a line from the specified stream and stores it into the string pointer to by str.
_
isspace()| checks whether a character is a white-space character or not.
_
strlen()| function calculates the length of a given string.
_
fork()| Fork system call is used for creating a new process, which is called child process.
_
execvp()| function duplicate the actions.
_
exit()| used to instantly end the calling process.
_
wait()| system call suspends execution of the calling thread until one of its children terminates.
.TE


